HEADWORD: Abietite
<hw>Ab"i*e*tite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A substance resembling mannite, found in the needles of the common
silver fir of Europe (<spn>Abies pectinata</spn>).</def> <rj><au>Eng.
Cyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

